# .claude — frontend-monorepo
#
# Project-level instructions for Claude / AI assistants working in this repo.

## Project overview
Next.js monorepo powered by Turborepo.
- `apps/web`                    — Main Next.js web application (port 3000)
- `apps/docs`                   — Documentation site (port 3001)
- `packages/ui`                 — Shared React component library
- `packages/eslint-config`      — Shared ESLint configuration
- `packages/typescript-config`  — Shared TypeScript configuration

## Stack
- Node.js 20+, npm 10+
- Next.js 16, React 19
- TypeScript 5.9
- Turborepo 2.x for task orchestration
- ESLint 9 (flat config), Prettier 3

## Key commands
```bash
npm install          # install all dependencies + register git hooks
npm run dev          # start all apps in dev mode
npm run build        # build all workspaces in dependency order
npm run lint         # ESLint across all workspaces
npm run check-types  # TypeScript across all workspaces
npm run test         # run all test suites
npm run format       # Prettier format all files
npm run clean        # remove all build artefacts
```

## Filter to a single workspace
```bash
npm run build -- --filter=@repo/web
npm run test  -- --filter=@repo/ui
```

## Code conventions
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, no implicit returns.
- All React components must be typed with explicit prop interfaces.
- Use named exports, not default exports (except Next.js pages).
- `singleQuote: false`, `trailingComma: "all"`, `semi: true` (see prettier.config.js).
- No `console.log` in production code.

## Adding a new workspace
1. Create directory under `apps/` or `packages/`.
2. Add `package.json` with a unique `name` starting with `@repo/`.
3. Run `npm install` from the repo root.

## Git conventions
- Conventional Commits: `feat(scope): description`
- Never commit directly to `main`.
- Tag format for package releases: `<package>-v<semver>`

## What NOT to do
- Do not add dependencies to the root `package.json` — they belong in workspaces.
- Do not bypass ESLint with `// eslint-disable` without a comment explaining why.
- Do not use `any` type — use `unknown` and narrow it.
